1
00:00:47,672 --> 00:00:50,967
THE APARTMENT JOB

2
00:00:52,051 --> 00:00:54,053
3 YEARS AGO

3
00:00:55,847 --> 00:00:57,640
Good morning, everyone.

4
00:01:01,811 --> 00:01:03,396
- Good morning, sir.
- Hi.

5
00:01:05,023 --> 00:01:06,106
Good morning, sir.

6
00:01:06,107 --> 00:01:07,316
What is this?

7
00:01:07,317 --> 00:01:09,193
We prepared this

8
00:01:09,194 --> 00:01:11,862
because today's VIP guest
is very interested in Korean heritage.

9
00:01:11,863 --> 00:01:15,074
Apparently, he's a Japanese yakuza,
and he's extremely wealthy.

10
00:01:15,075 --> 00:01:17,326
We'll make sure he becomes a regular.

11
00:01:17,327 --> 00:01:18,787
Tadayoshi…

12
00:01:19,871 --> 00:01:21,497
Be careful not to cause any commotion.

13
00:01:21,498 --> 00:01:22,706
- Yes, sir.
- Yes, sir.

14
00:01:22,707 --> 00:01:23,666
Be careful.

15
00:01:24,167 --> 00:01:25,251
Careful.

16
00:01:48,817 --> 00:01:50,692
This doesn't meet the dress code.

17
00:01:50,693 --> 00:01:51,777
Go back.

18
00:01:51,778 --> 00:01:54,238
We were invited by Mr. Kim.

19
00:01:54,239 --> 00:01:55,532
What is he saying?

20
00:01:57,826 --> 00:01:59,201
You think this is a spa?

21
00:01:59,202 --> 00:02:01,537
This place isn't for just anyone. Leave.

22
00:02:01,538 --> 00:02:04,206
Hey, who do you think we are?

23
00:02:04,207 --> 00:02:05,666
What the hell are you saying?

24
00:02:05,667 --> 00:02:07,000
Just leave.

25
00:02:07,001 --> 00:02:08,460
Mr. Tadayoshi!

26
00:02:08,461 --> 00:02:10,003
He's our VIP.

27
00:02:10,004 --> 00:02:11,589
Welcome!

28
00:02:12,173 --> 00:02:13,340
This way, sir.

29
00:02:13,341 --> 00:02:14,758
This way, please.

30
00:02:14,759 --> 00:02:15,718
Amazing.

31
00:02:16,761 --> 00:02:18,596
Awesome. Hang in there.

32
00:02:25,770 --> 00:02:27,271
We didn't know what you'd like,

33
00:02:27,272 --> 00:02:29,274
but you can assume
we've got everything you'd want.

34
00:02:29,858 --> 00:02:32,526
Roulette, baccarat, hold'em,

35
00:02:32,527 --> 00:02:34,444
go-stop, and poker.

36
00:02:34,445 --> 00:02:35,989
Tell us anything you'd like.

37
00:02:37,407 --> 00:02:39,534
Would you like some tea first, sir?

38
00:02:58,803 --> 00:03:00,805
Tadayoshi.

39
00:03:01,389 --> 00:03:02,764
I missed you.

40
00:03:02,765 --> 00:03:05,684
You won't make it back to Japan alive.

41
00:03:05,685 --> 00:03:08,270
Ichigaro, you followed me
all the way here?

42
00:03:08,271 --> 00:03:09,147
Fine.

43
00:03:09,981 --> 00:03:11,316
Let's end this here.

44
00:03:13,526 --> 00:03:14,652
Get him!

45
00:03:25,121 --> 00:03:25,997
What do we do?

46
00:03:50,980 --> 00:03:53,149
Hey! Kill that jerk first!

47
00:04:31,938 --> 00:04:32,772
Sayonara!

48
00:04:47,745 --> 00:04:48,579
Stop!

49
00:05:09,309 --> 00:05:10,893
We don't even know each other.

50
00:05:11,477 --> 00:05:12,895
Why did you save me?

51
00:05:13,646 --> 00:05:15,648
Because you're my customer.

52
00:05:26,159 --> 00:05:27,827
From now on,

53
00:05:28,786 --> 00:05:30,330
we're brothers.

54
00:05:31,748 --> 00:05:33,290
I promise

55
00:05:33,291 --> 00:05:34,917
to repay you someday.

56
00:05:43,426 --> 00:05:48,681
THE APARTMENT JOB

57
00:05:53,936 --> 00:05:55,687
- Thank you.
- Hello.

58
00:05:55,688 --> 00:05:57,023
Hello.

59
00:06:02,487 --> 00:06:04,530
I'm aching all over.

60
00:06:05,031 --> 00:06:07,867
You're the building rep now.
How long are we going to do this?

61
00:06:10,119 --> 00:06:12,830
You're the one who played a key role
in getting me elected.

62
00:06:13,414 --> 00:06:14,791
What do you mean?

63
00:06:18,377 --> 00:06:19,920
Hey, why are you running?

64
00:06:19,921 --> 00:06:22,256
I can run 100 meters in 10 seconds.
Don't you dare.

65
00:06:23,257 --> 00:06:24,841
Why were you chasing after us?

66
00:06:24,842 --> 00:06:26,427
You startled us.

67
00:06:28,137 --> 00:06:29,596
What's your deal?

68
00:06:29,597 --> 00:06:30,932
What?

69
00:06:31,474 --> 00:06:32,682
You took the video.

70
00:06:32,683 --> 00:06:34,643
Did you even get permission to upload it?

71
00:06:34,644 --> 00:06:36,812
Violating portrait rights, defamation,

72
00:06:36,813 --> 00:06:38,522
and spreading false information

73
00:06:38,523 --> 00:06:40,565
may result in up to two years
of imprisonment

74
00:06:40,566 --> 00:06:42,109
or a fine of up to five million won.

75
00:06:42,110 --> 00:06:43,944
Whatever. I'm a juvenile--

76
00:06:43,945 --> 00:06:46,739
Don't start with that
"juvenile offender" bullshit.

77
00:06:47,240 --> 00:06:48,366
Guys.

78
00:06:49,075 --> 00:06:51,159
You don't look anywhere

79
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:54,330
near the age of 14.

80
00:07:01,003 --> 00:07:03,255
This contains the truth about last night.

81
00:07:03,256 --> 00:07:05,299
I trust you to bring the truth to light.

82
00:07:07,426 --> 00:07:09,262
I heard everything
from the head of security.

83
00:07:10,263 --> 00:07:11,305
Thank you.

84
00:07:13,766 --> 00:07:16,936
It's not like I fabricated anything.

85
00:07:17,687 --> 00:07:21,149
I didn't have any other intentions.
You know I can't stand failure.

86
00:07:21,649 --> 00:07:22,859
Of course.

87
00:07:24,735 --> 00:07:27,071
I'll just do this
until I become the president.

88
00:07:27,572 --> 00:07:29,782
What will you do after that, then?

89
00:07:30,533 --> 00:07:33,828
I'll just let the delivery trucks enter
with my authority.

90
00:07:36,914 --> 00:07:40,000
<i>Breaking news.
Oman has been officially approved</i>

91
00:07:40,001 --> 00:07:42,294
<i>for the new town project.</i>

92
00:07:42,295 --> 00:07:45,797
<i>Many are describing this
as an unprecedented decision.</i>

93
00:07:45,798 --> 00:07:49,759
<i>The final approval of Oman New Town,
which had been excluded</i>

94
00:07:49,760 --> 00:07:52,596
<i>from the list of candidates
for the new town project,</i>

95
00:07:52,597 --> 00:07:55,640
<i>came as a surprise to the industry.</i>

96
00:07:55,641 --> 00:07:57,310
<i>- However, Oman…</i>
- Let's turn it off.

97
00:08:01,022 --> 00:08:01,856
It seems

98
00:08:02,899 --> 00:08:05,693
the assembly members
did their job right this time.

99
00:08:06,277 --> 00:08:08,820
My money finally paid off.

100
00:08:08,821 --> 00:08:09,989
Isn't this nice?

101
00:08:10,573 --> 00:08:12,574
Those who need money get paid,

102
00:08:12,575 --> 00:08:15,368
and they do their job properly in return.

103
00:08:15,369 --> 00:08:17,705
How fair is that?

104
00:08:19,207 --> 00:08:23,668
It's about time our association president
earned his keep as well.

105
00:08:23,669 --> 00:08:24,670
What is he up to?

106
00:08:26,923 --> 00:08:29,050
PRESIDENT SEO GANG-WON

107
00:08:31,135 --> 00:08:32,802
Yes, sir.

108
00:08:32,803 --> 00:08:35,348
<i>I hear Park Hae-kang
became the building rep.</i>

109
00:08:35,848 --> 00:08:37,933
This is so fun.

110
00:08:37,934 --> 00:08:39,602
I found him quite interesting.

111
00:08:40,186 --> 00:08:41,354
Well, I…

112
00:08:43,147 --> 00:08:44,356
Yes…

113
00:08:44,357 --> 00:08:45,482
<i>But President Seo,</i>

114
00:08:45,483 --> 00:08:48,443
this has to stop at just being fun.

115
00:08:48,444 --> 00:08:49,819
<i>You understand, don't you?</i>

116
00:08:49,820 --> 00:08:50,738
Well…

117
00:08:51,948 --> 00:08:53,365
Yes, sir.

118
00:08:53,366 --> 00:08:54,659
<i>Then first,</i>

119
00:08:55,243 --> 00:08:57,537
remove the restrictions
on the delivery trucks.

120
00:08:58,621 --> 00:09:02,707
But you're the one
who ordered those restrictions.

121
00:09:02,708 --> 00:09:05,168
<i>You said they were ruining
the landscaping.</i>

122
00:09:05,169 --> 00:09:06,754
Well, Park Hae-kang

123
00:09:07,547 --> 00:09:10,466
is getting on my nerves
more than the ruined landscaping.

124
00:09:11,467 --> 00:09:12,468
Got that?

125
00:09:21,185 --> 00:09:22,019
Mr. Kim.

126
00:09:23,354 --> 00:09:26,274
Maybe it's because I'm really petty,

127
00:09:26,857 --> 00:09:29,776
but I just can't stand anyone
being called a hero

128
00:09:29,777 --> 00:09:31,404
in my apartment complex.

129
00:09:33,197 --> 00:09:34,782
But this is bad.

130
00:09:36,284 --> 00:09:37,910
Park Hae-kang

131
00:09:39,829 --> 00:09:41,747
is becoming quite interesting.

132
00:09:44,625 --> 00:09:45,834
Enjoy.

133
00:09:45,835 --> 00:09:46,835
Thank you.

134
00:09:46,836 --> 00:09:50,380
You can even make
black bean noodles at home? Amazing.

135
00:09:50,381 --> 00:09:52,550
- I thought it was delivery.
- This is nothing.

136
00:09:53,217 --> 00:09:55,677
- Eat up, Gyeong-buk.
- Okay.

137
00:09:55,678 --> 00:09:58,346
You guys should eat up
to be ready for afternoon deliveries.

138
00:09:58,347 --> 00:09:59,348
- Yes, Boss.
- Yes, Boss.

139
00:10:01,058 --> 00:10:03,019
Eat up, son.

140
00:10:05,646 --> 00:10:07,148
It's too big.

141
00:10:08,441 --> 00:10:09,317
Is it too big?

142
00:10:11,652 --> 00:10:12,486
Gosh…

143
00:10:14,488 --> 00:10:15,488
I'll cut it for you.

144
00:10:15,489 --> 00:10:17,033
You're high-maintenance.

145
00:10:23,122 --> 00:10:24,582
FACILITY MANAGER

146
00:10:25,708 --> 00:10:27,500
What's the occasion, Mr. Choi?

147
00:10:27,501 --> 00:10:30,129
You don't have to make deliveries anymore.

148
00:10:30,921 --> 00:10:32,297
What?

149
00:10:32,298 --> 00:10:36,635
It doesn't look good to have
packages piled up at the entrance,

150
00:10:36,636 --> 00:10:39,804
and residents have been filing complaints.

151
00:10:39,805 --> 00:10:43,224
<i>So we decided to let
the delivery trucks enter again.</i>

152
00:10:43,225 --> 00:10:45,686
<i>I just needed to tell you that. Bye, then.</i>

153
00:10:51,275 --> 00:10:52,651
That was the facility manager.

154
00:10:52,652 --> 00:10:55,362
We don't have to do deliveries anymore.

155
00:10:55,363 --> 00:10:57,072
They're letting the trucks enter.

156
00:10:57,073 --> 00:10:58,658
Why? That's sudden.

157
00:10:59,158 --> 00:11:01,368
I don't know.
He said there were complaints.

158
00:11:01,369 --> 00:11:02,869
What complaints?

159
00:11:02,870 --> 00:11:05,956
I thought everyone was happy
with us delivering their packages.

160
00:11:06,540 --> 00:11:09,125
Well, if residents file complaints,

161
00:11:09,126 --> 00:11:11,336
the management office has no other choice.

162
00:11:11,337 --> 00:11:15,173
I guess some sensitive residents
were complaining again.

163
00:11:15,174 --> 00:11:16,966
Oh dear.

164
00:11:16,967 --> 00:11:20,054
But I guess we won't have
to make deliveries anymore.

165
00:11:23,057 --> 00:11:24,224
This is so good.

166
00:11:24,225 --> 00:11:26,393
You seem pretty excited.

167
00:11:26,394 --> 00:11:27,478
Is it just me?

168
00:11:29,897 --> 00:11:32,899
Couldn't you sense
the disappointment in my voice?

169
00:11:32,900 --> 00:11:36,861
I'm worried about
how you'll build your reputation now.

170
00:11:36,862 --> 00:11:40,573
But isn't our boss already quite famous
within the apartment complex now?

171
00:11:40,574 --> 00:11:43,953
He's right. No need to worry.
You've already built quite a reputation.

172
00:11:44,703 --> 00:11:46,705
I have to win over 9,800 households.

173
00:11:49,458 --> 00:11:51,585
Reputation alone won't be enough.

174
00:11:53,963 --> 00:11:55,881
I need something with more impact.

175
00:11:58,467 --> 00:11:59,301
Mr. Park.

176
00:11:59,969 --> 00:12:03,180
Stop acting all cool here and go outside.

177
00:12:04,181 --> 00:12:05,349
You two, go together.

178
00:12:05,850 --> 00:12:07,350
- Me too?
- Yes.

179
00:12:07,351 --> 00:12:09,895
Just go and greet all the residents.

180
00:12:10,479 --> 00:12:14,358
The basics of an election
are meeting voters in person.

181
00:12:18,821 --> 00:12:21,198
Don't you have a plan?
Are we just going to keep walking?

182
00:12:22,158 --> 00:12:23,242
I'm thinking.

183
00:12:24,243 --> 00:12:27,495
Let me give you some advice.

184
00:12:27,496 --> 00:12:29,914
Just walking like this
won't be of any use.

185
00:12:29,915 --> 00:12:32,292
You already have quite a reputation,

186
00:12:32,293 --> 00:12:34,961
so you should use that
to get more people on your side.

187
00:12:34,962 --> 00:12:36,045
My side?

188
00:12:36,046 --> 00:12:37,672
Like a faction.

189
00:12:37,673 --> 00:12:38,883
Or a support base.

190
00:12:41,760 --> 00:12:42,761
That's good.

191
00:12:43,637 --> 00:12:44,930
Let's get some supporters.

192
00:12:46,348 --> 00:12:48,766
Then let's head over there.

193
00:12:48,767 --> 00:12:50,560
There are lots of women gathered there.

194
00:12:50,561 --> 00:12:52,897
You can greet them
and have some coffee with them.

195
00:12:53,397 --> 00:12:54,314
Come on.

196
00:12:54,315 --> 00:12:56,150
My legs hurt from walking so much.

197
00:12:58,444 --> 00:13:01,279
- Congratulations.
- Congratulations.

198
00:13:01,280 --> 00:13:04,240
I can't believe you became
the building representative.

199
00:13:04,241 --> 00:13:06,117
It's nothing to be congratulated for.

200
00:13:06,118 --> 00:13:08,411
Why not? It's so cool.

201
00:13:08,412 --> 00:13:10,830
You're our representative.

202
00:13:10,831 --> 00:13:11,789
Right.

203
00:13:11,790 --> 00:13:14,834
You all know I was the sole candidate.

204
00:13:14,835 --> 00:13:17,045
In any case, I'm so relieved

205
00:13:17,046 --> 00:13:19,214
that you're our building rep.

206
00:13:19,215 --> 00:13:22,008
We can properly have our voices heard now.

207
00:13:22,009 --> 00:13:24,135
You should run
for association president as well.

208
00:13:24,136 --> 00:13:25,845
We'll support you all the way.

209
00:13:25,846 --> 00:13:26,972
- You should.
- Really.

210
00:13:28,224 --> 00:13:29,767
Don't be silly.

211
00:13:40,903 --> 00:13:42,071
Did you run for building rep?

212
00:13:42,821 --> 00:13:44,364
Yes.

213
00:13:44,365 --> 00:13:46,325
Did you see? I got elected.

214
00:13:47,034 --> 00:13:48,535
It's basically volunteer work.

215
00:13:48,536 --> 00:13:51,704
It's nothing difficult,
so you don't have to worry.

216
00:13:51,705 --> 00:13:53,082
Quit this, right now.

217
00:13:53,958 --> 00:13:54,874
What?

218
00:13:54,875 --> 00:13:56,125
Don't do it.

219
00:13:56,126 --> 00:13:59,963
I don't want you to do anything, honey.

220
00:13:59,964 --> 00:14:03,383
I just want you to sit still,
like a flower.

221
00:14:03,384 --> 00:14:05,928
Like a pretty houseplant. Okay?

222
00:14:09,765 --> 00:14:11,183
BUILDING REP ELECTION RESULTS NOTICE

223
00:14:14,144 --> 00:14:15,311
Yun-jo.

224
00:14:15,312 --> 00:14:16,522
Are you okay?

225
00:14:17,273 --> 00:14:19,440
I'm fine.

226
00:14:19,441 --> 00:14:22,986
Since we're on the topic, we should…

227
00:14:22,987 --> 00:14:24,654
Oh, it's that guy with the crazy kick.

228
00:14:24,655 --> 00:14:26,448
From District 4!

229
00:14:29,410 --> 00:14:31,119
Look how handsome he is.

230
00:14:31,120 --> 00:14:32,120
He's coming this way.

231
00:14:32,121 --> 00:14:34,957
He's so handsome. He looks like an actor.

232
00:14:35,541 --> 00:14:38,502
He looks like a model.

233
00:14:43,924 --> 00:14:45,009
Mr. Park.

234
00:14:46,010 --> 00:14:47,719
- Hello.
- Hello.

235
00:14:47,720 --> 00:14:50,513
Congratulations on getting elected.

236
00:14:50,514 --> 00:14:52,348
I should've lived in District 4.

237
00:14:52,349 --> 00:14:53,766
Me too.

238
00:14:53,767 --> 00:14:55,811
Thank you. I'm the guy who did that kick.

239
00:14:56,770 --> 00:14:57,980
Oh my gosh!

240
00:15:00,316 --> 00:15:01,649
The delivery hero.

241
00:15:01,650 --> 00:15:03,359
- A hero.
- It was so convenient.

242
00:15:03,360 --> 00:15:05,112
I don't know why I did that.

243
00:15:06,280 --> 00:15:08,532
I'm Park Hae-kang,
District 4's representative.

244
00:15:14,747 --> 00:15:15,748
Honey.

245
00:15:17,625 --> 00:15:19,251
I guess she can't hear me.

246
00:15:20,085 --> 00:15:21,420
Where the heck did he go?

247
00:15:22,171 --> 00:15:24,130
- Honey.
- "Honey"?

248
00:15:24,131 --> 00:15:25,257
That's so sweet.

249
00:15:26,425 --> 00:15:27,717
Ha-ri!

250
00:15:27,718 --> 00:15:28,761
"Ha-ri"?

251
00:15:36,060 --> 00:15:37,770
Hey, honey.

252
00:15:39,647 --> 00:15:40,813
Goodness.

253
00:15:40,814 --> 00:15:42,231
He even ran over to her.

254
00:15:42,232 --> 00:15:43,525
- That's so sweet.
- He's so sweet.

255
00:15:45,694 --> 00:15:47,904
- Hello.
- Hello.

256
00:15:47,905 --> 00:15:49,280
Isn't my wife beautiful?

257
00:15:49,281 --> 00:15:50,199
"Beautiful"?

258
00:15:51,241 --> 00:15:52,200
I rarely hear that.

259
00:15:52,201 --> 00:15:53,284
They're so sweet.

260
00:15:53,285 --> 00:15:55,244
- Do you want to sit here, honey?
- Sure.

261
00:15:55,245 --> 00:15:56,371
They look good together.

262
00:15:56,372 --> 00:15:57,455
It's like they're dating.

263
00:15:57,456 --> 00:15:59,082
- Right?
- They're so sweet.

264
00:15:59,083 --> 00:16:00,750
You must be newlyweds.

265
00:16:00,751 --> 00:16:02,335
You're so romantic.

266
00:16:02,336 --> 00:16:04,545
How long have you been married?

267
00:16:04,546 --> 00:16:05,756
- Eight…
- Six…

268
00:16:08,550 --> 00:16:10,344
- Has it been eight years already?
- Yes.

269
00:16:10,928 --> 00:16:13,930
I meant six years
after registering our marriage.

270
00:16:13,931 --> 00:16:15,056
How old is your kid?

271
00:16:15,057 --> 00:16:16,266
- Seven.
- Six.

272
00:16:18,227 --> 00:16:20,687
- He's six in international age.
- That's right.

273
00:16:20,688 --> 00:16:23,189
- Right, we use international age now.
- It's confusing.

274
00:16:23,190 --> 00:16:24,274
It's pretty confusing.

275
00:16:24,900 --> 00:16:27,152
Mr. Park, you're so handsome.

276
00:16:28,278 --> 00:16:30,114
I hear that often.

277
00:16:31,532 --> 00:16:34,076
But how did you two meet?

278
00:16:41,625 --> 00:16:43,459
It must have been somewhere embarrassing.

279
00:16:43,460 --> 00:16:44,669
A nightclub?

280
00:16:44,670 --> 00:16:45,713
- A nightclub?
- Is it?

281
00:16:46,463 --> 00:16:48,841
- That's ridiculous.
- I'm tearing up.

282
00:16:52,052 --> 00:16:53,970
<i>First encounter, library</i>

283
00:16:53,971 --> 00:16:55,638
<i>First kiss, under a street light</i>

284
00:16:55,639 --> 00:16:58,517
<i>Fateful encounter
At a book club after-party</i>

285
00:17:01,020 --> 00:17:04,105
Got it? We fell in love at first sight

286
00:17:04,106 --> 00:17:05,690
and felt that it was fate.

287
00:17:05,691 --> 00:17:06,567
Don't forget that.

288
00:17:07,776 --> 00:17:11,321
It's quite hard to believe
that I'd fall for you at first sight,

289
00:17:12,114 --> 00:17:13,906
but it's a safe story.

290
00:17:13,907 --> 00:17:14,949
Let's go with it.

291
00:17:14,950 --> 00:17:16,284
Hey.

292
00:17:16,285 --> 00:17:17,161
Your bonus.

293
00:17:18,120 --> 00:17:20,621
You worked hard delivering packages,

294
00:17:20,622 --> 00:17:22,373
and you came up with our backstory,

295
00:17:22,374 --> 00:17:24,709
so I'll give you a bonus.

296
00:17:24,710 --> 00:17:25,544
A bonus?

297
00:17:30,883 --> 00:17:33,384
I have my first
building rep meeting today,

298
00:17:33,385 --> 00:17:35,720
so take Gyeong-buk

299
00:17:35,721 --> 00:17:37,931
and put on a good mom act.

300
00:17:39,516 --> 00:17:40,392
Mom?

301
00:17:43,062 --> 00:17:46,064
Mom, I feel like I'm flying.

302
00:17:46,065 --> 00:17:48,316
No, you can't fly.

303
00:17:48,317 --> 00:17:49,734
I know that.

304
00:17:49,735 --> 00:17:51,194
I just meant this is nice.

305
00:17:51,195 --> 00:17:52,029
Right.

306
00:17:59,161 --> 00:18:00,829
- Ma'am.
- What?

307
00:18:01,455 --> 00:18:02,539
Isn't my mom pretty?

308
00:18:03,540 --> 00:18:05,541
Oh… Right.

309
00:18:05,542 --> 00:18:06,752
You're pretty too,

310
00:18:07,503 --> 00:18:09,296
but I think my mom's prettier.

311
00:18:10,422 --> 00:18:12,590
She's the prettiest
in our apartment complex.

312
00:18:12,591 --> 00:18:14,218
Stop that. Sorry.

313
00:18:14,927 --> 00:18:17,095
I guess you wanted to brag about your mom.

314
00:18:17,096 --> 00:18:19,889
Yes. Mom's really good at deboning fish,

315
00:18:19,890 --> 00:18:23,184
and she's super strong,
so she can carry heavy packages.

316
00:18:23,185 --> 00:18:25,854
And… my uncles all listen to her well.

317
00:18:26,897 --> 00:18:28,232
Even her name is pretty.

318
00:18:28,857 --> 00:18:31,568
Thank you, my son.

319
00:18:32,736 --> 00:18:34,279
Let's keep swinging.

320
00:18:36,490 --> 00:18:37,783
Bye.

321
00:18:44,206 --> 00:18:45,748
Mr. Park.

322
00:18:45,749 --> 00:18:47,875
Wow, you're dressed nicely.

323
00:18:47,876 --> 00:18:49,378
You'll really stand out.

324
00:18:49,962 --> 00:18:52,296
- Is it too much?
- It's way too much.

325
00:18:52,297 --> 00:18:54,799
But you have a handsome face,

326
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:57,552
so it might be effective
to use that as a weapon.

327
00:18:57,553 --> 00:18:58,595
Never mind that.

328
00:18:59,429 --> 00:19:01,889
I've never been
to a building rep meeting before.

329
00:19:01,890 --> 00:19:03,683
Is there anything
I need to be cautious of?

330
00:19:03,684 --> 00:19:04,892
Of course there is.

331
00:19:04,893 --> 00:19:07,728
That's why I prepared something for you.

332
00:19:07,729 --> 00:19:08,939
Sit down for a second.

333
00:19:14,403 --> 00:19:15,486
See this?

334
00:19:15,487 --> 00:19:16,904
Reappointed, reappointed,

335
00:19:16,905 --> 00:19:18,489
reappointed, reappointed.

336
00:19:18,490 --> 00:19:20,075
- Reappointed.
- So what?

337
00:19:23,203 --> 00:19:26,290
It means there's already
an established network in place.

338
00:19:26,874 --> 00:19:28,834
Look, all these people were reappointed.

339
00:19:29,710 --> 00:19:32,087
They've already made deals
among themselves.

340
00:19:32,588 --> 00:19:33,463
Let's see.

341
00:19:34,089 --> 00:19:35,965
He's the association president,

342
00:19:35,966 --> 00:19:37,466
and he's been reappointed too.

343
00:19:37,467 --> 00:19:39,970
So it's pretty obvious.

344
00:19:40,554 --> 00:19:42,305
This guy is the leader,

345
00:19:42,306 --> 00:19:44,557
and the others here will be flanking him

346
00:19:44,558 --> 00:19:46,852
like his bodyguards.

347
00:19:47,477 --> 00:19:50,313
There's already a close-knit cartel

348
00:19:50,314 --> 00:19:52,191
in this association.

349
00:19:55,319 --> 00:19:57,111
This won't be easy.

350
00:19:57,112 --> 00:20:00,365
You should brace yourself.
It's going to be a very lonely battle.

351
00:20:03,785 --> 00:20:06,537
DISTRICT 1, SEO GANG-WON

352
00:20:06,538 --> 00:20:08,915
TRUE VALUE STATE
4TH-TERM RESIDENTS' ASSOCIATION MEETING

353
00:20:08,916 --> 00:20:10,792
- It's been a while.
- Hello.

354
00:20:11,710 --> 00:20:12,878
Welcome.

355
00:20:14,421 --> 00:20:15,797
Welcome.

356
00:20:16,632 --> 00:20:22,011
Since this is the first meeting
for the new term of building reps,

357
00:20:22,012 --> 00:20:23,888
I'll wrap up the announcements here.

358
00:20:23,889 --> 00:20:26,558
We have
the most important agenda item left.

359
00:20:27,142 --> 00:20:29,436
We all know the election
for president is coming up.

360
00:20:30,187 --> 00:20:31,312
- Yes.
- Yes.

361
00:20:31,313 --> 00:20:35,650
Mr. Seo Gang-won,
who is our current association president,

362
00:20:35,651 --> 00:20:40,196
has decided to run for the position again.

363
00:20:40,197 --> 00:20:41,239
Round of applause.

364
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:42,574
Round of applause!

365
00:20:49,623 --> 00:20:53,752
We'll feel so reassured
if you continue as our president.

366
00:20:54,461 --> 00:20:56,170
<i>She's one of his guards.</i>

367
00:20:56,171 --> 00:21:00,007
Who else would be able
to take on such a difficult task?

368
00:21:00,008 --> 00:21:01,133
Exactly.

369
00:21:01,134 --> 00:21:02,301
<i>And he's one too.</i>

370
00:21:02,302 --> 00:21:04,136
I'm asking just in case.

371
00:21:04,137 --> 00:21:06,055
No one else is running, right?

372
00:21:06,056 --> 00:21:08,558
- No.
- No, sir.

373
00:21:13,021 --> 00:21:14,523
I will run as well.

374
00:21:15,357 --> 00:21:16,483
He's running…

375
00:21:17,359 --> 00:21:18,276
What?

376
00:21:18,277 --> 00:21:23,281
All right. Mr. Park Hae-kang
from District 4 will be running too.

377
00:21:23,282 --> 00:21:25,450
Is there anyone else?

378
00:21:31,373 --> 00:21:35,293
Just to be sure, Mr. Park Hae-kang,

379
00:21:35,294 --> 00:21:39,380
are you really going to run
for residents' association president?

380
00:21:39,381 --> 00:21:41,174
It won't be an easy job.

381
00:21:44,011 --> 00:21:45,887
Yes, I am.

382
00:21:48,265 --> 00:21:51,225
You're too young to be doing that.

383
00:21:51,226 --> 00:21:53,769
We won't vote for you
just because you're handsome.

384
00:21:53,770 --> 00:21:56,272
It's better for the former president
to continue.

385
00:21:56,273 --> 00:21:58,399
Not just anyone can do it.

386
00:21:58,400 --> 00:21:59,859
Right.

387
00:21:59,860 --> 00:22:01,610
<i>Will it be okay to just sit and watch?</i>

388
00:22:01,611 --> 00:22:05,156
I didn't expect Park Hae-kang
to run for president.

389
00:22:05,157 --> 00:22:08,284
President Seo,
Park Hae-kang is quite popular.

390
00:22:08,285 --> 00:22:11,662
He was called a delivery hero,
and with that kicking incident,

391
00:22:11,663 --> 00:22:13,581
he built quite a reputation.

392
00:22:13,582 --> 00:22:15,416
Shouldn't we do something as well?

393
00:22:15,417 --> 00:22:16,417
He's right.

394
00:22:16,418 --> 00:22:19,337
The residents will just vote
for the popular candidate.

395
00:22:19,338 --> 00:22:22,340
If Park Hae-kang really becomes
the president, it'll be a disaster.

396
00:22:22,341 --> 00:22:23,966
He could actually win at this rate.

397
00:22:23,967 --> 00:22:25,177
- Geez!
- Come on.

398
00:22:28,680 --> 00:22:30,306
CANDIDATE REGISTRATION FORM

399
00:22:30,307 --> 00:22:31,850
Any campaign pledge ideas?

400
00:22:33,018 --> 00:22:34,268
My opponent is President Seo.

401
00:22:34,269 --> 00:22:35,936
He's aiming for a fourth term.

402
00:22:35,937 --> 00:22:37,229
He's a strong opponent,

403
00:22:37,230 --> 00:22:40,025
so we need a bold pledge
that will grab everyone's attention.

404
00:22:42,944 --> 00:22:46,238
Last time, you said you'd make
a "very good apartment complex."

405
00:22:46,239 --> 00:22:48,950
This time, go for
a "very, very good apartment complex."

406
00:22:52,412 --> 00:22:54,747
Why don't you just say
"fantastic and amazing" instead?

407
00:22:54,748 --> 00:22:57,042
Are you kidding me?

408
00:22:57,626 --> 00:23:00,127
Campaign pledges don't mean anything.

409
00:23:00,128 --> 00:23:02,338
Don't you remember
class president elections?

410
00:23:02,339 --> 00:23:04,215
Kids didn't vote based on the pledges.

411
00:23:04,216 --> 00:23:07,552
They voted for candidates
who were handsome, popular, smart,

412
00:23:08,512 --> 00:23:09,678
or ate well.

413
00:23:09,679 --> 00:23:10,596
Kids like that.

414
00:23:10,597 --> 00:23:13,557
Nobody actually cares about the pledges.

415
00:23:13,558 --> 00:23:17,019
Boss, as the Lizard said,
I think you can write anything down.

416
00:23:17,020 --> 00:23:18,562
I believe he has a point.

417
00:23:18,563 --> 00:23:21,274
It's not like you got elected
because of your pledge.

418
00:23:30,742 --> 00:23:31,952
CANDIDATE PROFILE
PARK HAE-KANG

419
00:23:33,120 --> 00:23:34,995
IF I'VE TAKEN ANY BRIBES,
I'LL DONATE MY APARTMENT

420
00:23:34,996 --> 00:23:37,206
He'll donate his apartment?

421
00:23:37,207 --> 00:23:40,293
I know he's desperate to become
the president, but this is crazy.

422
00:23:50,262 --> 00:23:52,346
Park Hae-kang…

423
00:23:52,347 --> 00:23:54,682
He's the type who'll succeed in anything.

424
00:23:54,683 --> 00:23:56,350
He's bold.

425
00:23:56,351 --> 00:23:57,769
Now that's a real man.

426
00:24:01,314 --> 00:24:03,858
But I can't let him succeed

427
00:24:03,859 --> 00:24:05,819
in my apartment complex.

428
00:24:13,326 --> 00:24:14,493
Someone's coming!

429
00:24:14,494 --> 00:24:15,662
Gyeong-nam!

430
00:24:20,000 --> 00:24:21,917
- Hello.
- Hello.

431
00:24:21,918 --> 00:24:22,752
I'll take that.

432
00:24:23,795 --> 00:24:24,962
There's a lot, though.

433
00:24:24,963 --> 00:24:27,382
We should help each other as neighbors.

434
00:24:27,966 --> 00:24:30,343
- Thank you.
- Have a great day.

435
00:24:31,761 --> 00:24:33,263
- Plastic…
- Hello.

436
00:24:33,930 --> 00:24:35,265
How is your baby?

437
00:24:36,641 --> 00:24:38,894
Hello. Let me take that.

438
00:24:40,312 --> 00:24:41,730
I have hands too.

439
00:24:42,480 --> 00:24:43,522
It's nothing special.

440
00:24:43,523 --> 00:24:45,482
You're making such a fuss.

441
00:24:45,483 --> 00:24:46,318
Where is it?

442
00:24:46,943 --> 00:24:48,445
The plastic bin's over there…

443
00:24:55,702 --> 00:24:57,119
It's fine!

444
00:24:57,120 --> 00:24:58,663
What's with you?

445
00:25:07,130 --> 00:25:09,090
- Thank you for everything.
- Sure.

446
00:25:20,727 --> 00:25:23,271
Is it already time
to discuss a contract renewal?

447
00:25:23,980 --> 00:25:26,315
That's actually why we dropped by.

448
00:25:26,316 --> 00:25:30,486
How will you choose
the contractor this time, sir?

449
00:25:30,487 --> 00:25:31,654
What do you mean?

450
00:25:31,655 --> 00:25:34,031
We'll go through a fair bidding process.

451
00:25:34,032 --> 00:25:35,242
Sir.

452
00:25:36,785 --> 00:25:40,788
I'm sure you can easily pull
some strings for this.

453
00:25:40,789 --> 00:25:42,831
I don't have any power.

454
00:25:42,832 --> 00:25:43,792
Come on.

455
00:25:48,255 --> 00:25:49,380
I was just kidding.

456
00:25:49,381 --> 00:25:52,801
Of course I can pull
a few strings for you guys.

457
00:25:53,677 --> 00:25:54,970
Thank you, sir.

458
00:25:59,975 --> 00:26:02,643
I'm pretty sure it's him.

459
00:26:02,644 --> 00:26:03,644
What?

460
00:26:03,645 --> 00:26:05,604
His name's Park Hae-kang.

461
00:26:05,605 --> 00:26:07,189
It really is him.

462
00:26:07,190 --> 00:26:09,275
No wonder he seemed familiar.

463
00:26:09,276 --> 00:26:10,402
Hang on.

464
00:26:11,569 --> 00:26:13,570
- Do you know him?
- Yes.

465
00:26:13,571 --> 00:26:16,283
He was the boss of the Oasis Gang.

466
00:26:16,992 --> 00:26:18,492
The Oasis Gang?

467
00:26:18,493 --> 00:26:19,952
Yes.

468
00:26:19,953 --> 00:26:22,496
I wondered how he was living
after retirement.

469
00:26:22,497 --> 00:26:23,414
What a surprise.

470
00:26:23,415 --> 00:26:24,790
But this guy

471
00:26:24,791 --> 00:26:27,209
must have earned quite some money
to be living here.

472
00:26:27,210 --> 00:26:28,544
Right.

473
00:26:28,545 --> 00:26:30,380
- Are you sure about this?
- Yes.

474
00:26:34,217 --> 00:26:35,844
All done.

475
00:26:36,720 --> 00:26:38,430
Today was the toughest.

476
00:26:40,223 --> 00:26:41,558
What's this?

477
00:26:42,934 --> 00:26:44,561
An urgent meeting?

478
00:26:45,562 --> 00:26:47,147
The building reps have to attend?

479
00:26:48,565 --> 00:26:50,566
<i>This is the management office.</i>

480
00:26:50,567 --> 00:26:53,277
<i>Today's building representative meeting</i>

481
00:26:53,278 --> 00:26:57,614
<i>will include an important agenda item
regarding the election,</i>

482
00:26:57,615 --> 00:27:01,785
<i>so it will be broadcast
for all households to watch.</i>

483
00:27:01,786 --> 00:27:03,412
<i>We will appreciate your attention.</i>

484
00:27:03,413 --> 00:27:06,415
- They're broadcasting the meeting?
<i>- Thank you.</i>

485
00:27:06,416 --> 00:27:07,751
Is something going on?

486
00:27:08,376 --> 00:27:11,628
They wouldn't do such a thing
unless it's really important.

487
00:27:11,629 --> 00:27:12,546
Do I have to go?

488
00:27:12,547 --> 00:27:13,964
Of course you do.

489
00:27:13,965 --> 00:27:15,383
You should get ready, Boss.

490
00:27:18,178 --> 00:27:22,057
All right. Let's begin
the building representatives' meeting.

491
00:27:22,807 --> 00:27:23,974
What's the urgent issue?

492
00:27:23,975 --> 00:27:27,312
The president will explain it now.

493
00:27:30,774 --> 00:27:36,236
Thank you all for attending
when you must be busy.

494
00:27:36,237 --> 00:27:39,491
Our boss really stands out
among all those people.

495
00:27:40,909 --> 00:27:43,370
That's because of his flashy jacket.

496
00:27:44,371 --> 00:27:46,164
He's the youngest.

497
00:27:46,915 --> 00:27:51,293
<i>We called this emergency meeting today</i>

498
00:27:51,294 --> 00:27:52,503
<i>because the residents</i>

499
00:27:52,504 --> 00:27:54,129
<i>- have the right to know.</i>
- "Soccer."

500
00:27:54,130 --> 00:27:58,008
<i>- A very troubling incident has occurred.</i>
- Oh my.

501
00:27:58,009 --> 00:28:03,222
<i>- Something outrageous has happened here.</i>
- He's so handsome.

502
00:28:03,223 --> 00:28:07,476
Among the building representatives
who were elected this time,

503
00:28:07,477 --> 00:28:11,314
there's someone
who submitted false credentials.

504
00:28:19,781 --> 00:28:22,241
What's with that annoying smirk?

505
00:28:22,242 --> 00:28:25,327
Who submitted false credentials?

506
00:28:25,328 --> 00:28:27,996
If someone really did,
that's a huge problem.

507
00:28:27,997 --> 00:28:29,581
Tell us who it is.

508
00:28:29,582 --> 00:28:34,086
I apologize once again
for having to bring up

509
00:28:34,087 --> 00:28:35,754
such an uncomfortable matter.

510
00:28:35,755 --> 00:28:37,340
But Mr. Park Hae-kang,

511
00:28:38,383 --> 00:28:41,969
I heard you were the boss
of the Oasis Gang,

512
00:28:41,970 --> 00:28:45,889
which was a nationwide gang

513
00:28:45,890 --> 00:28:47,725
that was even on the news.

514
00:28:47,726 --> 00:28:49,144
Gosh, it's hot!

515
00:28:50,019 --> 00:28:52,522
He got caught.

516
00:28:53,148 --> 00:28:54,941
You…

517
00:28:57,235 --> 00:28:59,069
used to be the boss of a gang.

518
00:28:59,070 --> 00:29:03,491
Why did you hide that fact from everyone?

519
00:29:04,743 --> 00:29:06,368
- A gang?
- A gang?

520
00:29:06,369 --> 00:29:09,080
A gang? Goodness.

521
00:29:10,206 --> 00:29:12,916
Goodness gracious.

522
00:29:12,917 --> 00:29:13,960
Oh my gosh.

523
00:29:18,089 --> 00:29:19,007
A gang?

524
00:29:19,966 --> 00:29:21,426
I can't believe this.

525
00:29:24,345 --> 00:29:25,472
Oh my.

526
00:29:27,098 --> 00:29:30,476
I've… retired.

527
00:29:30,477 --> 00:29:33,437
But it's true you were in a gang.

528
00:29:33,438 --> 00:29:35,814
They say people never change.

529
00:29:35,815 --> 00:29:38,567
I'm so scared. I'm getting the chills.

530
00:29:38,568 --> 00:29:40,861
I can't believe there's a thug here.

531
00:29:40,862 --> 00:29:42,613
- Enough of that.
- Gosh.

532
00:29:42,614 --> 00:29:46,867
How would the residents trust you
to manage the apartment complex?

533
00:29:46,868 --> 00:29:50,454
How can a thug represent
the 9,800 households here?

534
00:29:50,455 --> 00:29:52,206
Withdraw your candidacy immediately!

535
00:29:52,207 --> 00:29:53,541
- Step down.
- Step down!

536
00:29:57,796 --> 00:29:58,963
Everyone!

537
00:30:00,298 --> 00:30:01,465
Calm down.

538
00:30:01,466 --> 00:30:04,760
Let's hear what he has to say first.

539
00:30:04,761 --> 00:30:08,138
I'm sure Mr. Park
would have had his own reasons.

540
00:30:08,139 --> 00:30:10,099
Right? Go on.

541
00:30:13,394 --> 00:30:15,771
Mr. Park?

542
00:30:15,772 --> 00:30:17,689
You should at least say something

543
00:30:17,690 --> 00:30:22,111
for us to know
whether or not this is true…

544
00:30:22,987 --> 00:30:23,947
First of all,

545
00:30:26,115 --> 00:30:28,200
I'm sorry for causing concern over this--

546
00:30:28,201 --> 00:30:29,827
Mr. Park.

547
00:30:29,828 --> 00:30:32,580
Please stand up and speak politely.

548
00:30:34,624 --> 00:30:36,250
Come on. Stand up.

549
00:30:36,251 --> 00:30:37,919
Stand up and talk.

550
00:30:40,421 --> 00:30:41,755
Stand up.

551
00:30:41,756 --> 00:30:44,717
Can't you hear me? Stand up.

552
00:30:54,727 --> 00:30:55,770
I…

553
00:30:56,479 --> 00:30:57,355
used to be

554
00:30:58,523 --> 00:30:59,899
in a gang,

555
00:31:01,568 --> 00:31:02,861
but that's in the past…

556
00:31:09,450 --> 00:31:10,618
- What?
- What's going on?

557
00:31:12,161 --> 00:31:14,413
What is it?

558
00:31:14,414 --> 00:31:17,249
The power suddenly went out. Hang on.

559
00:31:17,250 --> 00:31:18,375
Right.

560
00:31:18,376 --> 00:31:20,294
- Fix it.
- I think it's this.

561
00:31:20,295 --> 00:31:22,838
Then I guess we have no choice.

562
00:31:22,839 --> 00:31:27,302
Due to equipment issues,
we won't be able to broadcast the rest.

563
00:31:43,359 --> 00:31:44,776
Did you see the look on his face?

564
00:31:44,777 --> 00:31:46,905
He was as pale as a sheet.

565
00:31:47,864 --> 00:31:50,365
He'll have no choice but to withdraw.

566
00:31:50,366 --> 00:31:53,286
Withdrawing won't be the problem.
He'll have to move out.

567
00:31:53,953 --> 00:31:56,580
But why did you keep
such important information

568
00:31:56,581 --> 00:31:58,248
to yourself, sir?

569
00:31:58,249 --> 00:31:59,374
Right?

570
00:31:59,375 --> 00:32:00,918
If you'd told us in advance,

571
00:32:00,919 --> 00:32:03,588
we could've crushed him
on the spot back there.

572
00:32:04,339 --> 00:32:06,173
That was enough.

573
00:32:06,174 --> 00:32:08,133
He would have understood my words.

574
00:32:08,134 --> 00:32:11,428
You're just too generous, President Seo.

575
00:32:11,429 --> 00:32:12,638
How about a toast?

576
00:32:12,639 --> 00:32:14,515
- Cheers.
- Sure.

577
00:32:15,558 --> 00:32:17,727
- Cheers.
- Cheers.

578
00:32:18,728 --> 00:32:19,687
Bottoms up.

579
00:32:22,982 --> 00:32:23,900
We're screwed.

580
00:32:24,859 --> 00:32:25,776
We're screwed.

581
00:32:25,777 --> 00:32:26,944
Our gang…

582
00:32:26,945 --> 00:32:28,487
I mean, what do we do now?

583
00:32:28,488 --> 00:32:31,782
Since it's come to this,
can I just start packing?

584
00:32:31,783 --> 00:32:32,909
You little…

585
00:32:33,952 --> 00:32:34,953
Boss.

586
00:32:36,579 --> 00:32:38,455
Why couldn't you say anything?

587
00:32:38,456 --> 00:32:40,874
Why couldn't you say
that you're just an ordinary guy now

588
00:32:40,875 --> 00:32:42,250
who wants to be the president?

589
00:32:42,251 --> 00:32:43,585
I didn't have the chance to.

590
00:32:43,586 --> 00:32:45,879
Still, you could've just denied--

591
00:32:45,880 --> 00:32:48,048
You should've just denied it.

592
00:32:48,049 --> 00:32:50,133
- Then we can announce--
- No.

593
00:32:50,134 --> 00:32:52,427
Don't you want to be the president?

594
00:32:52,428 --> 00:32:54,763
There's no rule that says
you can't be the president

595
00:32:54,764 --> 00:32:55,931
if you were in a gang.

596
00:32:55,932 --> 00:32:58,016
And leaking private info
can land you two years

597
00:32:58,017 --> 00:32:59,559
or a fine of five million.

598
00:32:59,560 --> 00:33:01,269
Anyway, let's sue him first.

599
00:33:01,270 --> 00:33:03,397
Let's sue him!

600
00:33:03,398 --> 00:33:04,898
Ms. Kang, calm down…

601
00:33:04,899 --> 00:33:07,109
How can I calm down right now?

602
00:33:07,110 --> 00:33:08,151
Aren't you even angry?

603
00:33:08,152 --> 00:33:10,571
How dare they do this
in front of everyone?

604
00:33:11,239 --> 00:33:12,657
Ms. Kang.

605
00:33:15,368 --> 00:33:17,744
You guys,
look into how President Seo found out.

606
00:33:17,745 --> 00:33:19,080
- Yes, Boss.
- Yes, Boss.

607
00:33:19,664 --> 00:33:21,498
You passed the criminal background check,

608
00:33:21,499 --> 00:33:24,459
so they can't revoke your candidacy
just because they want to.

609
00:33:24,460 --> 00:33:26,254
The problem is public opinion.

610
00:33:29,424 --> 00:33:31,800
- He was in a gang.
- That kick.

611
00:33:31,801 --> 00:33:32,969
- He kicked him…
- A gang.

612
00:33:34,971 --> 00:33:36,389
Hello.

613
00:33:37,724 --> 00:33:38,599
Hi.

614
00:33:58,536 --> 00:34:00,037
I forgot my wallet!

615
00:34:00,038 --> 00:34:02,330
- She has a stomachache.
- I forgot my phone.

616
00:34:02,331 --> 00:34:03,875
- I forgot my laundry.
- Me too.

617
00:34:06,044 --> 00:34:07,045
But it's the fifth floor.

618
00:34:07,962 --> 00:34:09,881
- What? I can't believe it.
- Seriously.

619
00:34:11,090 --> 00:34:12,467
Goodness!

620
00:34:13,676 --> 00:34:15,720
Public opinion really is scary.

621
00:34:16,763 --> 00:34:17,972
I knew this would happen.

622
00:34:20,600 --> 00:34:22,101
Hello.

623
00:34:23,186 --> 00:34:24,896
Could I sit here?

624
00:34:25,980 --> 00:34:27,148
Yes, sure.

625
00:34:29,275 --> 00:34:31,485
- It's not like she did anything wrong.
- Right.

626
00:34:31,486 --> 00:34:33,780
Love isn't a sin.

627
00:34:35,031 --> 00:34:38,116
But did you know when you married him?

628
00:34:38,117 --> 00:34:40,327
Were you deceived, by any chance?

629
00:34:40,328 --> 00:34:41,953
- What?
- He doesn't…

630
00:34:41,954 --> 00:34:43,580
beat you or anything, does he?

631
00:34:43,581 --> 00:34:46,166
Oh, gosh. Then he'd be a real scumbag.

632
00:34:46,167 --> 00:34:47,834
That's crazy.

633
00:34:47,835 --> 00:34:50,253
That explains that kick.

634
00:34:50,254 --> 00:34:52,339
Right. He didn't seem
like an ordinary guy.

635
00:34:52,340 --> 00:34:54,257
What a waste of a handsome face.

636
00:34:54,258 --> 00:34:56,343
Why did he live like that
with such good looks?

637
00:34:56,344 --> 00:34:58,095
- Right?
- A gang? Seriously?

638
00:34:58,096 --> 00:34:59,722
- Hang on…
- Right.

639
00:35:00,306 --> 00:35:01,598
You should get divorced.

640
00:35:01,599 --> 00:35:03,392
- That's the only way.
- She's right.

641
00:35:04,977 --> 00:35:05,812
I…

642
00:35:06,354 --> 00:35:09,106
love his past as well.

643
00:35:09,107 --> 00:35:10,190
You know,

644
00:35:10,191 --> 00:35:12,484
someone's past isn't what's important.

645
00:35:12,485 --> 00:35:15,196
It's how you overcome your past
and live in the present.

646
00:35:15,780 --> 00:35:18,073
He doesn't do stuff like that anymore.

647
00:35:18,074 --> 00:35:20,575
He's responsible,
family-oriented, hardworking,

648
00:35:20,576 --> 00:35:21,827
and handsome.

649
00:35:21,828 --> 00:35:22,911
Right.

650
00:35:22,912 --> 00:35:25,123
He's the perfect husband.

651
00:35:25,623 --> 00:35:27,582
We were just worried about you, is all.

652
00:35:27,583 --> 00:35:29,668
There's no need to worry.

653
00:35:29,669 --> 00:35:32,712
I'll stand by my decision
until the very end.

654
00:35:32,713 --> 00:35:35,591
I chose him, and we're doing our best.

655
00:35:36,801 --> 00:35:39,262
Don't be quick to judge people
who are working hard.

656
00:35:40,012 --> 00:35:40,929
By the way,

657
00:35:40,930 --> 00:35:43,431
I married him
because I fell for his awesome kicks.

658
00:35:43,432 --> 00:35:44,267
My goodness.

659
00:35:48,563 --> 00:35:50,648
- They really are a couple.
- They're so alike.

660
00:35:55,820 --> 00:35:57,445
What was that?

661
00:35:57,446 --> 00:36:01,075
Did I just defend Park Hae-kang
because we're a family, even if it's fake?

662
00:36:03,327 --> 00:36:04,370
Unbelievable.

663
00:36:06,914 --> 00:36:08,499
Someone's coming, Boss!

664
00:36:10,168 --> 00:36:12,544
Hello. Let me take that for you.

665
00:36:12,545 --> 00:36:14,796
It's fine. I can do it.

666
00:36:14,797 --> 00:36:16,340
- I'll do it.
- No, it's fine.

667
00:36:18,801 --> 00:36:20,303
Let me take that.

668
00:36:22,096 --> 00:36:22,930
All right.

669
00:36:26,684 --> 00:36:28,269
- Have a nice day.
- Thank you.

670
00:36:47,205 --> 00:36:48,830
You know,

671
00:36:48,831 --> 00:36:51,000
if you make others suffer,

672
00:36:51,918 --> 00:36:54,212
it'll come back to haunt you.

673
00:36:55,379 --> 00:36:56,214
Me?

674
00:36:58,591 --> 00:37:00,342
- What are you talking about?
- It was you.

675
00:37:00,343 --> 00:37:01,677
What do you mean?

676
00:37:02,345 --> 00:37:05,389
You're the one who uploaded
that post about academic fraud.

677
00:37:07,516 --> 00:37:11,811
You're the one
who lied about the deliveries first.

678
00:37:11,812 --> 00:37:14,105
I really did graduate
from Ilhwa Women's University

679
00:37:14,106 --> 00:37:15,649
at the top of my class.

680
00:37:15,650 --> 00:37:17,485
And I really worked hard to deliver…

681
00:37:22,240 --> 00:37:24,366
You can't defeat President Seo
at this rate.

682
00:37:24,367 --> 00:37:26,826
Elections are all about public opinion.

683
00:37:26,827 --> 00:37:29,496
But you've already lost there,
like I have.

684
00:37:29,497 --> 00:37:31,123
Serves you right.

685
00:37:32,792 --> 00:37:34,961
You really are frustrating.

686
00:37:36,128 --> 00:37:37,420
What do you mean?

687
00:37:37,421 --> 00:37:40,924
You have no idea
how much President Seo and his cronies

688
00:37:40,925 --> 00:37:43,636
ruined our apartment complex
and how much they pocketed.

689
00:37:44,845 --> 00:37:47,389
I can't stand to see them
continue on like this.

690
00:37:47,390 --> 00:37:49,057
This is so frustrating.

691
00:37:49,058 --> 00:37:51,018
But it's not like I can trust you either.

692
00:37:53,729 --> 00:37:54,605
Let's go.

693
00:37:55,439 --> 00:37:56,481
Where?

694
00:37:56,482 --> 00:37:57,857
Will you do nothing, then?

695
00:37:57,858 --> 00:37:59,651
You have to at least try something.

696
00:37:59,652 --> 00:38:01,696
Where's your fighting spirit?

697
00:38:02,363 --> 00:38:03,698
Follow me. Come on.

698
00:38:07,076 --> 00:38:08,452
Follow me.

699
00:38:09,120 --> 00:38:10,830
It's not anywhere bad. Come on.

700
00:38:16,752 --> 00:38:20,297
Move Oman Station Line 10, Exit 3

701
00:38:20,298 --> 00:38:22,215
to True Value State!

702
00:38:22,216 --> 00:38:25,135
- Move Exit 3 to True Value State!
- Move Exit 3 to True Value State!

703
00:38:25,136 --> 00:38:27,929
Withdraw the Oman Station

704
00:38:27,930 --> 00:38:30,015
exit announcement!

705
00:38:30,016 --> 00:38:37,522
- Withdraw the announcement!
- Withdraw the announcement!

706
00:38:37,523 --> 00:38:39,566
True Value!

707
00:38:39,567 --> 00:38:44,654
- True Value!
- True Value!

708
00:38:44,655 --> 00:38:47,032
What am I even doing here?

709
00:38:47,033 --> 00:38:51,161
- Exit 3!
- Exit 3!

710
00:38:51,162 --> 00:38:52,246
MOVE EXIT 3 TO TRUE VALUE

711
00:38:53,372 --> 00:38:55,332
This looks delicious.

712
00:38:55,333 --> 00:38:58,126
It was tough protesting
in such cold weather, wasn't it?

713
00:38:58,127 --> 00:39:00,879
Since we had a new member join us today,

714
00:39:00,880 --> 00:39:02,422
I'm treating everyone.

715
00:39:02,423 --> 00:39:03,798
Enjoy.

716
00:39:03,799 --> 00:39:05,133
You're paying again?

717
00:39:05,134 --> 00:39:06,676
Let's just split the bill.

718
00:39:06,677 --> 00:39:08,636
Don't say that.

719
00:39:08,637 --> 00:39:09,804
Come on.

720
00:39:09,805 --> 00:39:12,724
Once the exit is built
right in front of our apartment complex,

721
00:39:12,725 --> 00:39:14,476
housing prices will go through the roof.

722
00:39:14,477 --> 00:39:18,480
Jang Suk-jin from True Value
can pay for this much. Right?

723
00:39:18,481 --> 00:39:20,023
All right, fine.

724
00:39:20,024 --> 00:39:21,608
Eat up, everyone.

725
00:39:21,609 --> 00:39:22,734
Okay.

726
00:39:22,735 --> 00:39:25,487
Why is Ms. Park calling me again?

727
00:39:25,488 --> 00:39:27,739
Let me take this call. Eat up, everyone.

728
00:39:27,740 --> 00:39:28,990
- Thanks.
- Sure.

729
00:39:28,991 --> 00:39:31,701
- Enjoy.
- Hello, it's Jang Suk-jin.

730
00:39:31,702 --> 00:39:32,911
Yes.

731
00:39:32,912 --> 00:39:34,788
<i>Why am I eating this right now?</i>

732
00:39:34,789 --> 00:39:37,957
Excuse me.
It's my first time joining the protest.

733
00:39:37,958 --> 00:39:41,044
Is it really possible that the subway exit

734
00:39:41,045 --> 00:39:43,547
will be moved to True Value instead?

735
00:39:44,757 --> 00:39:45,841
No.

736
00:39:47,218 --> 00:39:49,220
Then why are we doing this?

737
00:39:50,846 --> 00:39:52,014
It's fun.

738
00:39:52,848 --> 00:39:54,683
We get to hang out and eat together.

739
00:39:55,643 --> 00:39:56,810
Oh, stop.

740
00:39:56,811 --> 00:39:58,104
Welcome.

741
00:39:58,604 --> 00:40:02,982
Well, unless some kind of cultural relic
is dug up in Oman New Town,

742
00:40:02,983 --> 00:40:05,026
a finalized plan
wouldn't be changed that easily…

743
00:40:05,027 --> 00:40:05,986
<i>Relic?</i>

744
00:40:13,702 --> 00:40:16,621
<i>Relics were once discovered in Busan</i>

745
00:40:16,622 --> 00:40:18,706
<i>during subway construction,</i>

746
00:40:18,707 --> 00:40:22,169
<i>so new town projects
ended up being canceled or delayed.</i>

747
00:40:22,878 --> 00:40:25,047
<i>Anyway, they need to discover some relics.</i>

748
00:40:32,263 --> 00:40:33,472
No, not you.

749
00:40:34,432 --> 00:40:36,558
- Is something going on?
- You two.

750
00:40:36,559 --> 00:40:38,768
You need to go to Japan immediately.

751
00:40:38,769 --> 00:40:40,145
- What?
- Japan?

752
00:40:40,146 --> 00:40:41,188
Yes.

753
00:40:56,829 --> 00:40:59,331
Long time no see.

754
00:41:00,166 --> 00:41:01,332
- Hello.
- Hi.

755
00:41:01,333 --> 00:41:02,209
Hi. This way, please.

756
00:41:21,937 --> 00:41:23,272
<i>Sir, we're connected.</i>

757
00:41:25,316 --> 00:41:27,026
- Boss.
<i>- Okay. I can see you.</i>

758
00:41:32,031 --> 00:41:33,991
It's been a while, Park Hae-kang.

759
00:41:34,867 --> 00:41:36,327
Explain to me

760
00:41:37,369 --> 00:41:38,745
what's going on right now.

761
00:41:38,746 --> 00:41:40,705
I'll keep it simple.

762
00:41:40,706 --> 00:41:42,582
We're brothers, aren't we?

763
00:41:42,583 --> 00:41:44,042
Though I, Tadayoshi,

764
00:41:44,043 --> 00:41:47,045
do not share blood with you,
Park Hae-kang,

765
00:41:47,046 --> 00:41:48,756
you are my brother

766
00:41:49,882 --> 00:41:51,300
whom I swore to protect.

767
00:41:54,345 --> 00:41:57,181
I will give you a chance
to repay that debt.

768
00:41:57,932 --> 00:42:00,976
<i>I need your help this time.</i>

769
00:42:01,602 --> 00:42:03,103
Anything you say.

770
00:42:03,687 --> 00:42:04,939
Who do you want dead?

771
00:42:05,523 --> 00:42:07,733
The Korean relic you have…

772
00:42:08,442 --> 00:42:09,860
I need it.

773
00:42:18,494 --> 00:42:19,953
This jerk.

774
00:42:19,954 --> 00:42:21,080
<i>Tadayoshi.</i>

775
00:42:21,664 --> 00:42:23,164
The real one, not a fake one.

776
00:42:23,165 --> 00:42:25,668
Brothers shouldn't
deceive each other like this.

777
00:42:30,839 --> 00:42:34,843
You truly do deserve to be my brother.

778
00:42:38,681 --> 00:42:40,015
What? Where's he…

779
00:42:46,564 --> 00:42:47,897
- My leg. Boss.
- Boss.

780
00:42:47,898 --> 00:42:50,109
Tadayoshi just left. What's going on?

781
00:42:54,655 --> 00:42:57,073
Boss, how did you know this was a fake?

782
00:42:57,074 --> 00:42:58,908
He brought that in with his bare hands.

783
00:42:58,909 --> 00:42:59,993
But look now.

784
00:42:59,994 --> 00:43:02,121
<i>He's carrying that one with gloves.</i>

785
00:43:12,464 --> 00:43:13,591
<i>Tadayoshi.</i>

786
00:43:28,814 --> 00:43:30,064
Hello.

787
00:43:30,065 --> 00:43:31,775
- Hello.
- Hello.

788
00:43:34,737 --> 00:43:36,571
I knew it.

789
00:43:36,572 --> 00:43:38,407
Young people lack perseverance.

790
00:43:43,287 --> 00:43:44,370
- Hello.
- Hello.

791
00:43:44,371 --> 00:43:46,122
- You went out this morning?
- Yes.

792
00:43:46,123 --> 00:43:47,290
- See you around.
- Ma'am.

793
00:43:47,291 --> 00:43:48,666
- Gosh!
- What took you so long?

794
00:43:48,667 --> 00:43:50,418
I've been waiting for you.

795
00:43:50,419 --> 00:43:53,838
You weren't over there, so…

796
00:43:53,839 --> 00:43:55,673
Fine. Just look at me.

797
00:43:55,674 --> 00:43:56,716
Look at me.

798
00:43:56,717 --> 00:43:58,343
- What's this about?
- Look at me.

799
00:43:58,344 --> 00:44:00,219
All right. Ta-da.

800
00:44:00,220 --> 00:44:02,472
Ms. Jang Suk-jin…

801
00:44:02,473 --> 00:44:05,309
- Welcome!
- Welcome!

802
00:44:05,893 --> 00:44:06,727
Goodness.

803
00:44:07,686 --> 00:44:08,895
What is this?

804
00:44:08,896 --> 00:44:12,398
Move Oman Station
Line 10, Exit 3 to True Value!

805
00:44:12,399 --> 00:44:14,692
- True Value!
- True Value!

806
00:44:14,693 --> 00:44:17,320
Withdraw the decision
that ignored the residents' voices!

807
00:44:17,321 --> 00:44:19,698
- Withdraw the decision!
- Withdraw the decision!

808
00:44:21,742 --> 00:44:23,785
- You're here.
- What's going on here?

809
00:44:23,786 --> 00:44:26,579
I don't know.
How did you know we were doing this?

810
00:44:26,580 --> 00:44:28,956
I told them to come here.

811
00:44:28,957 --> 00:44:31,292
- My gosh.
- Thank you all for coming.

812
00:44:31,293 --> 00:44:33,086
Here. Pass these around

813
00:44:33,087 --> 00:44:35,296
and distribute them to passersby.

814
00:44:35,297 --> 00:44:37,048
Let's do this.

815
00:44:37,049 --> 00:44:38,133
This way.

816
00:44:41,887 --> 00:44:44,430
Move Oman Station
Line 10, Exit 3 to True Value!

817
00:44:44,431 --> 00:44:46,265
- True Value!
- True Value!

818
00:44:46,266 --> 00:44:49,102
Withdraw the decision
that ignored the residents' voices!

819
00:44:49,103 --> 00:44:50,938
- Withdraw the decision!
- Withdraw the decision!

820
00:44:54,942 --> 00:44:57,861
Withdraw the decision
that ignored the residents' voices!

821
00:45:08,497 --> 00:45:11,500
- Park Hae-kang leads us to victory!
- Park Hae-kang leads us to victory!

822
00:45:13,168 --> 00:45:14,836
- Park Hae-kang!
- Park Hae-kang!

823
00:45:14,837 --> 00:45:17,880
Move Exit 3 to True Value!

824
00:45:17,881 --> 00:45:20,591
- True Value!
- True Value!

825
00:45:20,592 --> 00:45:22,218
Do you need anything else?

826
00:45:22,219 --> 00:45:23,719
No, thank you.

827
00:45:23,720 --> 00:45:25,596
- Mr. Park!
- Yes?

828
00:45:25,597 --> 00:45:28,599
We need more <i>gimbap</i> here!

829
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:29,935
Coming!

830
00:45:32,521 --> 00:45:33,605
There's some here.

831
00:45:39,111 --> 00:45:40,778
- This is good.
- Thank you.

832
00:45:40,779 --> 00:45:42,739
- Is it good?
- Is it good?

833
00:45:53,167 --> 00:45:54,418
Oh, gosh!

834
00:45:57,463 --> 00:45:58,713
My goodness.

835
00:45:58,714 --> 00:46:00,382
Why did you fall?

836
00:46:01,049 --> 00:46:02,133
He fell!

837
00:46:02,134 --> 00:46:03,385
Are you okay?

838
00:46:04,386 --> 00:46:05,803
Are you hurt?

839
00:46:05,804 --> 00:46:08,181
Yes. But what is that?

840
00:46:08,182 --> 00:46:09,683
What did I trip on?

841
00:46:10,517 --> 00:46:13,020
Gosh, it must have been this.

842
00:46:13,896 --> 00:46:15,021
What is that?

843
00:46:15,022 --> 00:46:16,023
What is this?

844
00:46:16,607 --> 00:46:19,067
Goodness…

845
00:46:22,821 --> 00:46:23,655
What is this?

846
00:46:24,656 --> 00:46:26,408
It looks like they found something.

847
00:46:30,454 --> 00:46:31,371
Wait…

848
00:46:33,373 --> 00:46:35,459
It looks really old.

849
00:46:36,210 --> 00:46:37,710
What is this?

850
00:46:37,711 --> 00:46:39,337
- It looks like some kind of relic.
- Relic?

851
00:46:39,338 --> 00:46:41,380
- We found a relic?
- A relic?

852
00:46:41,381 --> 00:46:42,549
- A relic!
- A relic!

853
00:46:45,844 --> 00:46:48,804
They must have found a relic!

854
00:46:48,805 --> 00:46:49,848
Mr. Park.

855
00:46:50,516 --> 00:46:53,393
Something incredible has just happened.

856
00:46:54,478 --> 00:46:59,232
Everyone! Report this to the media!

857
00:46:59,233 --> 00:47:00,358
Hurry! Report this!

858
00:47:00,359 --> 00:47:02,277
Our house prices are going to soar!

859
00:47:15,916 --> 00:47:19,210
I think we've dug quite a bit.
Do we dig more?

860
00:47:19,211 --> 00:47:20,420
Dig the deepest over there.

861
00:47:21,588 --> 00:47:24,215
Make the depths different
so they'll keep getting discovered.

862
00:47:24,216 --> 00:47:26,717
Mr. Park, why don't I

863
00:47:26,718 --> 00:47:30,137
just get a good price for this
from a fence I know?

864
00:47:30,138 --> 00:47:31,514
We can use the money…

865
00:47:31,515 --> 00:47:32,683
Should I bury you in there?

866
00:47:36,562 --> 00:47:37,771
Boss.

867
00:47:38,939 --> 00:47:40,648
Will this really work, though?

868
00:47:40,649 --> 00:47:42,900
If apartment prices soar
after they're discovered,

869
00:47:42,901 --> 00:47:45,444
everyone will forget
that I used to be in a gang.

870
00:47:45,445 --> 00:47:48,614
I'll just be the guy
who helped raise the apartment prices.

871
00:47:48,615 --> 00:47:52,201
This is the only thing
that can flip public opinion about me

872
00:47:52,202 --> 00:47:53,786
in one shot.

873
00:47:53,787 --> 00:47:55,329
- So dig.
- Yes, Boss!

874
00:47:55,330 --> 00:47:56,455
- Yes, Boss!
- Yes, Boss!

875
00:47:56,456 --> 00:47:57,541
Yes, sir!

876
00:47:58,041 --> 00:48:03,088
- Let's dig.
- Let's dig.

877
00:48:11,179 --> 00:48:12,638
JOEUN REAL ESTATE

878
00:48:12,639 --> 00:48:13,723
They discovered relics.

879
00:48:13,724 --> 00:48:15,891
They'll reconsider the subway exit.

880
00:48:15,892 --> 00:48:20,187
Of course. They have no choice
but to change it to True Value.

881
00:48:20,188 --> 00:48:22,690
Today is the cheapest it'll ever be.

882
00:48:22,691 --> 00:48:24,525
- Oman New Town…
- They found relics.

883
00:48:24,526 --> 00:48:26,527
So development will be put to a stop.

884
00:48:26,528 --> 00:48:29,196
The probability of the exit
being changed to True Value is…

885
00:48:29,197 --> 00:48:30,782
- 90%.
- 90%.

886
00:48:32,826 --> 00:48:34,119
It's starting.

887
00:48:36,997 --> 00:48:41,417
<i>A variety of artifacts, such as pottery,
iron swords, and arrowheads,</i>

888
00:48:41,418 --> 00:48:43,419
<i>have been excavated
from the Oman New Town site.</i>

889
00:48:43,420 --> 00:48:46,339
<i>The discovery was made in an area
with no prior historical research,</i>

890
00:48:46,340 --> 00:48:49,133
<i>so historians are also deeply confused.</i>

891
00:48:49,134 --> 00:48:52,928
<i>Even in our field,
this is an unexpected find.</i>

892
00:48:52,929 --> 00:48:56,057
<i>Through a full investigation of the site,
we'll be able to determine</i>

893
00:48:56,058 --> 00:48:59,810
<i>the historical relationship
between the finds and the location.</i>

894
00:48:59,811 --> 00:49:00,978
<i>I was just walking by…</i>

895
00:49:00,979 --> 00:49:02,271
It's him!

896
00:49:02,272 --> 00:49:04,690
<i>I just tripped on something
and fell like this.</i>

897
00:49:04,691 --> 00:49:07,027
<i>That relic was just buried right there.</i>

898
00:49:08,070 --> 00:49:10,529
<i>With the unexpected discovery
of the cultural artifact,</i>

899
00:49:10,530 --> 00:49:13,574
<i>the new town development
is expected to be put on hold for now,</i>

900
00:49:13,575 --> 00:49:18,580
<i>and the subway exit for Oman Station,
Line 10, is likely to be reconsidered.</i>

901
00:49:23,669 --> 00:49:26,170
How on earth did you discover that
at just the right time?

902
00:49:26,171 --> 00:49:28,632
I guess I can say I was lucky.

903
00:49:29,966 --> 00:49:31,968
He made that luck.

904
00:49:33,512 --> 00:49:34,429
Lizard.

905
00:49:35,097 --> 00:49:39,058
I mean, heaven helps
those who help themselves,

906
00:49:39,059 --> 00:49:40,769
so I guess the earth

907
00:49:41,978 --> 00:49:44,063
also created that for you.

908
00:49:44,064 --> 00:49:46,441
That's what I meant.

909
00:49:47,567 --> 00:49:49,235
Anyway, congratulations.

910
00:49:49,236 --> 00:49:51,529
You might actually become
the president at this rate.

911
00:49:51,530 --> 00:49:54,657
Boss, the apartment complex forum
is filled with comments about you.

912
00:49:54,658 --> 00:49:55,951
Let me see.

913
00:49:56,910 --> 00:50:00,287
"The true hero who saved True Value,
Park Hae-kang."

914
00:50:00,288 --> 00:50:02,331
"Park Hae-kang is better than my own son."

915
00:50:02,332 --> 00:50:05,419
"The next residents' association president
should be Park Hae-kang."

916
00:50:06,420 --> 00:50:08,879
You've truly become
the hottest guy in True Value.

917
00:50:08,880 --> 00:50:10,090
He's like a celebrity!

918
00:50:12,884 --> 00:50:15,428
Stop spilling crumbs while eating snacks.

919
00:50:15,429 --> 00:50:17,556
Why do I always have
to clean up after you?

920
00:50:18,265 --> 00:50:21,017
We're going to have cockroaches in here
because of you!

921
00:50:21,518 --> 00:50:24,520
I applaud you all

922
00:50:24,521 --> 00:50:28,232
for working so hard.

923
00:50:28,233 --> 00:50:30,359
Cheers!

924
00:50:30,360 --> 00:50:32,821
- Cheers!
- Cheers!

925
00:50:39,369 --> 00:50:43,038
The heavens have answered our prayers,
don't you think?

926
00:50:43,039 --> 00:50:46,584
If you hadn't suggested protesting,
this would never have happened.

927
00:50:46,585 --> 00:50:49,837
Right. Mr. Park should know
that it was all thanks to you.

928
00:50:49,838 --> 00:50:51,464
I'm sure he knows.

929
00:50:51,465 --> 00:50:53,008
Eat up, everyone.

930
00:50:53,759 --> 00:50:55,217
Enjoy.

931
00:50:55,218 --> 00:50:57,094
My son.

932
00:50:57,095 --> 00:50:58,095
You're home.

933
00:50:58,096 --> 00:50:59,013
Hello.

934
00:50:59,014 --> 00:51:01,891
I'm in a great mood today.

935
00:51:01,892 --> 00:51:07,605
Our apartment prices have soared.

936
00:51:07,606 --> 00:51:08,689
Have some meat.

937
00:51:08,690 --> 00:51:09,732
- Come here.
- Sit.

938
00:51:09,733 --> 00:51:11,484
It's fine. Enjoy your dinner.

939
00:51:11,485 --> 00:51:12,861
Gosh.

940
00:51:13,653 --> 00:51:15,529
He's really shy.

941
00:51:15,530 --> 00:51:17,073
Kids these days are so shy.

942
00:51:20,285 --> 00:51:22,662
Development is going to be put on hold

943
00:51:23,246 --> 00:51:25,290
until the excavation
and investigation are complete

944
00:51:25,916 --> 00:51:27,209
because of the relics.

945
00:51:28,251 --> 00:51:30,544
I checked the relevant laws and past cases

946
00:51:30,545 --> 00:51:32,546
on buried cultural assets,

947
00:51:32,547 --> 00:51:36,134
but there's nothing we can really do
for the next three years.

948
00:51:43,725 --> 00:51:45,519
I guess I can't fit…

949
00:51:48,647 --> 00:51:50,440
the last piece of my puzzle.

950
00:52:15,090 --> 00:52:18,509
Why did they have to find
a damn relic over there?

951
00:52:18,510 --> 00:52:21,136
I can't believe this.

952
00:52:21,137 --> 00:52:22,763
This is driving me crazy.

953
00:52:22,764 --> 00:52:24,598
What should we do?

954
00:52:24,599 --> 00:52:27,309
The subway exit
is likely to be moved to True Value now.

955
00:52:27,310 --> 00:52:30,980
Everyone's talking about Park Hae-kang
being the president because of this.

956
00:52:30,981 --> 00:52:33,148
They're not even bringing
up the gang anymore.

957
00:52:33,149 --> 00:52:37,278
They were the ones saying
a former thug couldn't be the president.

958
00:52:37,279 --> 00:52:39,698
Look how fickle they are.

959
00:52:41,700 --> 00:52:43,326
The election is tomorrow.

960
00:52:44,244 --> 00:52:48,206
Park Hae-kang might actually
become the president at this rate.

961
00:52:48,999 --> 00:52:51,542
Why would you say that?

962
00:52:51,543 --> 00:52:53,544
You'll just bring bad luck by saying that!

963
00:52:53,545 --> 00:52:57,048
Park Hae-kang can never
become the president. Never!

964
00:52:59,134 --> 00:53:02,219
Get out, all of you!

965
00:53:02,220 --> 00:53:03,346
Bye, sir.

966
00:53:07,726 --> 00:53:09,810
DAY OF THE PRESIDENT ELECTION

967
00:53:09,811 --> 00:53:12,187
4TH-TERM RESIDENTS' ASSOCIATION
PRESIDENT ELECTION

968
00:53:12,188 --> 00:53:13,857
1 SEO GANG-WON, 2 PARK HAE-KANG

969
00:53:17,736 --> 00:53:18,695
BALLOT DISTRIBUTION

970
00:53:26,953 --> 00:53:30,831
CANDIDATE 2, PARK HAE-KANG

971
00:53:30,832 --> 00:53:32,709
BALLOT

972
00:53:33,418 --> 00:53:34,668
All right.

973
00:53:34,669 --> 00:53:36,629
Don't drop the ballot yet.

974
00:53:36,630 --> 00:53:38,673
Smile a little more, please.

975
00:53:39,925 --> 00:53:45,888
CANDIDATE 1, SEO GANG-WON

976
00:53:45,889 --> 00:53:47,432
VOTING BOX
SEO GANG-WON

977
00:54:26,137 --> 00:54:27,597
It's 6:00, Boss.

978
00:54:28,848 --> 00:54:29,808
Is it posted?

979
00:54:31,017 --> 00:54:32,935
<i>This is the management office.</i>

980
00:54:32,936 --> 00:54:36,480
<i>We would like to inform you
that Park Hae-kang from District 4</i>

981
00:54:36,481 --> 00:54:40,192
<i>has been elected as the new
residents' association president.</i>

982
00:54:40,193 --> 00:54:41,027
Yes!

983
00:54:50,495 --> 00:54:51,495
Thank you.

984
00:54:51,496 --> 00:54:53,707
Congratulations.

985
00:54:54,457 --> 00:54:55,708
You did it, Boss!

986
00:54:55,709 --> 00:54:57,419
- You did it!
- We did it!

987
00:54:58,003 --> 00:54:59,336
Congratulations, Mr. Park.

988
00:54:59,337 --> 00:55:02,632
You finally got the position
that you wanted so badly.

989
00:55:03,174 --> 00:55:04,342
It's all thanks to you.

990
00:55:04,968 --> 00:55:06,719
Is my job over now, then?

991
00:55:06,720 --> 00:55:08,345
Well,

992
00:55:08,346 --> 00:55:10,305
wouldn't people think it strange

993
00:55:10,306 --> 00:55:12,307
if my wife suddenly disappeared?

994
00:55:12,308 --> 00:55:15,729
Why don't you work
for about two more weeks?

995
00:55:16,438 --> 00:55:19,273
Well, if you pay me for the extra days,

996
00:55:19,274 --> 00:55:20,774
that won't be difficult.

997
00:55:20,775 --> 00:55:23,111
Of course, you'll be paid for it.

998
00:55:24,320 --> 00:55:26,238
Ms. Kang, we should throw a party today.

999
00:55:26,239 --> 00:55:28,490
I'll make an amazing dinner tonight.

1000
00:55:28,491 --> 00:55:29,867
Join us if you have time.

1001
00:55:29,868 --> 00:55:31,411
Yes, sure.

1002
00:55:31,911 --> 00:55:34,039
Don't cook.
Just order everything you want to eat.

1003
00:55:37,375 --> 00:55:40,419
Sorry, but can you give me an autograph?

1004
00:55:40,420 --> 00:55:43,631
Shouldn't we have some drinks
to celebrate tonight?

1005
00:55:44,215 --> 00:55:45,508
I'll go buy the drinks.

1006
00:55:46,468 --> 00:55:47,843
We can't send you out for that.

1007
00:55:47,844 --> 00:55:48,803
Thank you.

1008
00:55:50,847 --> 00:55:53,683
The leading intellectual of our time,
Park Hae-kang.

1009
00:56:01,858 --> 00:56:03,943
RESIDENTS' ASSOCIATION PRESIDENT'S OFFICE

1010
00:56:09,074 --> 00:56:10,158
Ta-da.

1011
00:56:13,703 --> 00:56:14,579
Sir.

1012
00:56:18,333 --> 00:56:20,460
A historic turnout

1013
00:56:21,503 --> 00:56:23,837
of 74%,

1014
00:56:23,838 --> 00:56:28,008
and an overwhelming 90% of the vote.

1015
00:56:28,009 --> 00:56:30,969
While Park Hae-kang achieved all of this,

1016
00:56:30,970 --> 00:56:33,848
what exactly were you doing?

1017
00:56:35,183 --> 00:56:37,017
I'm really sorry,

1018
00:56:37,018 --> 00:56:39,812
but I believe

1019
00:56:39,813 --> 00:56:41,188
I can flip the results.

1020
00:56:41,189 --> 00:56:43,148
So if you trust me, I'll…

1021
00:56:43,149 --> 00:56:44,442
No.

1022
00:56:45,568 --> 00:56:46,486
I…

1023
00:56:46,986 --> 00:56:50,697
can't stand those who take my money

1024
00:56:50,698 --> 00:56:53,952
and don't do their job.

1025
00:56:58,248 --> 00:56:59,165
Sir.

1026
00:57:01,209 --> 00:57:03,335
I'm really sorry.

1027
00:57:03,336 --> 00:57:06,213
But honestly, don't you think

1028
00:57:06,214 --> 00:57:09,133
I've been doing a good job so far?

1029
00:57:09,134 --> 00:57:11,301
Sir, please…

1030
00:57:11,302 --> 00:57:13,011
Mr. Lee!

1031
00:57:13,012 --> 00:57:14,638
Sir, please…

1032
00:57:14,639 --> 00:57:16,390
Please give me another chance.

1033
00:57:16,391 --> 00:57:18,143
Mr. Lee…

1034
00:57:19,769 --> 00:57:21,728
You won't need this anymore.

1035
00:57:21,729 --> 00:57:23,106
Just one more chance…

1036
00:57:35,285 --> 00:57:36,494
How do you like that?

1037
00:57:49,549 --> 00:57:50,550
Hello.

1038
00:57:52,218 --> 00:57:53,344
Mr. Park.

1039
00:57:54,345 --> 00:57:55,221
Well…

1040
00:57:56,723 --> 00:57:58,308
I heard the good news.

1041
00:57:58,975 --> 00:57:59,933
Congratulations.

1042
00:57:59,934 --> 00:58:01,519
You already heard?

1043
00:58:04,689 --> 00:58:05,523
<i>Blood?</i>

1044
00:58:16,201 --> 00:58:18,243
You must be on your way home from work.

1045
00:58:18,244 --> 00:58:20,580
I had some business
at the management office, and…

1046
00:58:28,046 --> 00:58:30,089
Well, goodnight.

1047
00:58:30,673 --> 00:58:31,758
Right.

1048
00:58:35,512 --> 00:58:36,846
Mr. Park.

1049
00:58:38,306 --> 00:58:39,265
Yes?

1050
00:58:42,185 --> 00:58:44,229
Congratulations

1051
00:58:45,813 --> 00:58:47,941
on being elected president.

1052
00:58:49,734 --> 00:58:51,568
Thank you.

1053
00:58:51,569 --> 00:58:52,779
Goodnight, then.

1054
00:58:53,863 --> 00:58:54,906
Mr. Park?

1055
00:58:55,865 --> 00:58:56,908
Yes?

1056
00:59:05,291 --> 00:59:06,417
We'll…

1057
00:59:07,544 --> 00:59:09,712
be seeing each other again.

1058
00:59:39,701 --> 00:59:42,453
THE APARTMENT JOB

1059
01:00:06,561 --> 01:00:08,186
<i>But why is that guy going so far</i>

1060
01:00:08,187 --> 01:00:11,148
<i>as to fake a family to become
a residents' association president?</i>

1061
01:00:11,149 --> 01:00:12,691
It's beautiful.

1062
01:00:12,692 --> 01:00:15,319
"Apartment complexes,
a hotbed of corruption!"

1063
01:00:15,320 --> 01:00:19,072
<i>Not writing up contracts properly,
embezzling maintenance funds…</i>

1064
01:00:19,073 --> 01:00:22,159
<i>So please,
don't get involved in such corruption.</i>

1065
01:00:22,160 --> 01:00:23,869
<i>-Gyeong-nam, prepare a bag.
- Yes, sir.</i>

1066
01:00:23,870 --> 01:00:26,330
<i>-Big Guy, sell off everything in the home.
- Yes, sir.</i>

1067
01:00:26,331 --> 01:00:28,457
<i>Je-gil, get the facility manager's stamp.</i>

1068
01:00:28,458 --> 01:00:30,042
<i>"Power never lasts."</i>

1069
01:00:30,043 --> 01:00:35,005
I'm offering to manage
your family risk for you.

1070
01:00:35,006 --> 01:00:38,175
<i>It's almost impossible
for such relics to be found here.</i>

1071
01:00:38,176 --> 01:00:40,802
So someone planted them on purpose?

1072
01:00:40,803 --> 01:00:42,804
<i>If I catch whoever did this…</i>

1073
01:00:42,805 --> 01:00:44,222
Ms. Kang.

1074
01:00:44,223 --> 01:00:45,891
<i>I'm going to kill them.</i>

1075
01:00:45,892 --> 01:00:48,645
<i>We'll hit the bank in the morning,
get the money, and leave immediately.</i>

1076
01:00:51,731 --> 01:00:53,733
Subtitle translation by: Juyoung Park
